When you already have a perfect shape but still looking for improvement 😊
For years I have been using ink cups on cotton round instead of ink holder. Who does the same?

Lip mapping is an essential part of the lip blush procedure. Creating clean lines and ensuring symmetrical sides are crucial for instilling trust in your expertise. Upon completing the mapping, I always double-check my work. I ask the client to:

1. Smile
2. Make an “O”
3. Make a kissing motion
4. Take a picture and conduct one final check

All these steps will help in creating a clean and symmetrical shape.
The satisfying process of creating a thin outline and that first pass 😍
Lip blush enhances natural lip color, providing a subtle and long-lasting tint. It's a popular choice for achieving those "juicy lips" without the need for constant reapplication.

Clients frequently ask, “Can I choose the color?” 
The answer is, “Of course, you can!” 
My suggestion is to bring your favorite lipsticks or find and save some pictures online. I always conduct a consultation before we begin the work. Together, we will review various color examples and select the one you like best. I recommend a more natural look for your first appointment, and if you desire, we can go bolder during your touch-up.
Healed Lips 💋
Before/After on beautiful girl 💋

Tiny outline on upper lip and first pass on bottom lips. Creating a tiny outline especially on the upper lip can be challenging in lip blushing. Achieving a crisp outline is one of the most difficult aspects, requiring time and practice to develop the precision needed for a precise line.

What to expect during your lip blush appointment?

Consultation. During consultation we talk about your goals and all the steps of the process. 
Mapping. After mapping is completed, you can see how your shape is improved.
Shading. We start with petite outline then do from 3-5 passes. Every pass is numb. 
Aftercare. You leave home with aftercare kit and detailed instructions.

Questions? Contact to get a consultation before your appointment. 😊

Lip Transformation: A request from my client was to create a more even color and shape. She has struggled with cold sores for years, resulting in a lot of scar tissue and pigment loss. Lip Blush is a great service that can help resolve this issue and make you feel more comfortable.
